# Data Analyst Agent

A simple Streamlit app that lets you ask questions about your CSV/Excel files in plain English and get SQL-powered answers.

## What it does

- Upload a CSV or Excel file
- Ask questions like "What are the top 5 sales?" or "Show me average by category"
- Get automatic SQL queries and results
- See AI-generated insights about your data

## Setup

1. Install requirements:
```bash
pip install streamlit pandas openai openpyxl
```

2. Get an OpenAI API key from https://platform.openai.com/account/api-keys

3. Run the app:
```bash
streamlit run data_analyst_agent.py
```

4. Open http://localhost:8501 in your browser

## How to use

1. Enter your OpenAI API key in the sidebar
2. Upload your data file
3. Type your question about the data
4. Get results and insights automatically

## Example questions

- "What are the top 10 records by [column name]?"
- "Show me the average of [column] by [other column]"
- "How many unique values are in [column]?"
- "What records have [column] greater than 100?"

